93	  \emph{Exactness at the middle.} Exactness of a short complex of sheaves of modules is detected stalkwise: a short complex is exact iff it is exact on every stalk. On each stalk we are reduced to the ring-level exactness $\Omega_{A'/A} \otimes_{A'} B \to \Omega_{B/A} \to \Omega_{B/A'} \to 0$ provided by Mathlib's \texttt{KaehlerDifferential.exact\_mapBaseChange\_map}. The stalkwise-exactness criterion is a small Mathlib-gap-fill (Lemma~\ref{lem:sheafOfModules_exact_iff_stalkwise} below).
94	
95	  \emph{Surjectivity of $\beta$.} Epimorphism is reflected through the faithful forgetful functor $\mathrm{SheafOfModules} \to \mathrm{PresheafOfModules}$: it suffices to show $\beta.\mathrm{val}$ is an epi of presheaves. The latter follows from \texttt{PresheafOfModules.epi\_iff\_surjective} together with the descent identification of $\beta_U$ with $\mathrm{KaehlerDifferential.map}\,\eta_U\,\mathrm{id}$ provided by the coherence square of Lemma~\ref{lem:cotangent_exact_seq_beta_hη} (where $\eta$ is the natural ring map and the right-hand component is the identity, so surjectivity reduces to \texttt{KaehlerDifferential.map\_surjective}). The reflection step is a small Mathlib-gap-fill (Lemma~\ref{lem:sheafOfModules_epi_of_epi_presheaf} below).
96	\end{proof}
